Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Install Python and pytest for the checker
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        python3-setuptools \
        python3-wheel --no-install-recommends
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare initial filesystem state for the exercise
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Create /home/user with world-writable permissions so the
    # non-privileged runtime user can add the required artefacts later.
    mkdir -p /home/user
    chmod 777 /home/user

    # Create the api_samples directory with the three JSON stubs
    mkdir -p /home/user/api_samples

    cat >/home/user/api_samples/sample1.json <<'EOF'
{
  "id": 1,
  "status": "ok",
  "data": "alpha"
}
EOF

    cat >/home/user/api_samples/sample2.json <<'EOF'
{
  "id": 2,
  "status": "ok",
  "data": "beta"
}
EOF

    cat >/home/user/api_samples/sample3.json <<'EOF'
{
  "id": 3,
  "status": "ok",
  "data": "gamma"
}
EOF

    # Read-only access is sufficient for the sample files themselves
    chmod 755 /home/user/api_samples
    chmod 644 /home/user/api_samples/sample*.json

%labels
    Author  API-backup exercise container

%help
    This Apptainer container provides the initial environment for the
    “API backup” exercise.  It contains:
      • /home/user/api_samples/ with three predefined JSON files
      • pytest installed for automated checking
    Students will create additional artefacts (tar archive, restore
    directory, log file) during the exercise runtime.